      • addType

        public ReflectParameterTypes addType(java.lang.String clazzName,
                            java.lang.ClassLoader loader)
                              throws ReflectParameterTypes.ReflectParameterException
        Add a parameter type based on it's full class name. The method will locate the class object associated with the name and add it to the parameter list.
        Parameters:
        clazzName - The name of the class type
        loader - ClassLoader to use for the search or NULL to use ReflectClass default
        Throws:
        ReflectParameterTypes.ReflectParameterException - This is thrown if ReflectClass was unable to resolve the class name

      • addType

        Add a Class object representing a parameter type
        Parameters:
        clazz - The Class object that should be added to the parameter list

      • addResolveType

        public ReflectParameterTypes addResolveType(java.lang.Object argument)
        Locates the Class object of an unknown argument. Use this if you have an unknown argument/variable which should be converted into a Class representing a parameter type
        Parameters:
        argument - An unknown argument/variable
